  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Our Common Home: Partner Engagement</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Our Common Home is CAFOD&apos;s new strategic framework currently under development to guide our activities, programs and partnerships for the next 5 - 10 years. OCH principles is rooted in scripture and Catholic Social teaching promoting human dignity, fundamental equality of men and women, responsibility of one another as a global family and stewardship of creation. Our Common Home is our response to the 2015 papal encyclical Laudato Si&#x2019; . Pope Francis states that &#x201C;We are faced not with two separate crises, one environmental and the other social, but rather with one complex crisis which is both social and environmental. Strategies for a solution demand an integrated approach to combating poverty, restoring dignity to the excluded, and at the same time protecting nature&#x201D;. 

The planned engagement with partners is to get them to understand and also get their voices in terms in improving ad/or challenging the strategy.</narrative>
  </description>
